      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TENNESSEE DOLLY (8) resumes and has raced well in stronger company. Fitter for two trials, missing a lip at Warwick Farm most recently. Will be naturally improved and looks well placed to break through. SIX KINGS (3) is an improver in the Maher stable back 180m in trip. He races forward and has more to give. Looked a run short at Orange 10-days ago. KOSRAE (6) has to manage the outside gate but looks primed to go following two sharp trials. Just missed over 1200m at Kembla Grange when last seen and is sure to have come on. ARTISTIC LADY (4) disappointed at Wyong 11-days ago at big odds but improved, beaten 1.8L at Newcastle prior. She has an awkward barrier but peaks for this, and the shorter sprint is likely to suit. BORDER TOWN (2) has been off the scene for 1489-days and will go a lot better second-up. Had switched from the Snowden barn and has a low gate and Hutchings aboard. Must be showing something.",
